reviewText: All these cooking shows on TV, they really are nice, but cooking food really destroys the nutritional value of the food I've been eating all my life. The process of packaging food destroys the food I've been eating also. For decades I have been filling the VOID (my stomach) but I have not been eating nutricious food. WE ALL can benifit emensely if we shop at farmers markets or grow our own food. It is a bit more expensive, but so is medical care and treatment for having a bad diet.
Title: Raw For Life: The Ultimate Encyclopedia of the Raw Food Lifestyle

reviewText: This is okay. If you want to hear people talk. Is it great!!! Not at all. it is a lot of interviews with 6 different Celebrity & Expert interviews.
Title: Raw For Life: The Ultimate Encyclopedia of the Raw Food Lifestyle

reviewText: recipes were ok. Comments were ok.The movie was better. Wasnt as much as I expected.I eat raw and I have much easier and tastier recipes.

reviewText: I BOUGHT THIS THINKING IT WAS THE MOVIE RAW FOR 30 DAYS, SORTA A REVIRSE OF THE MOVIE SUPER SIZE ME WHICH WAS FANTASTIC. I WATCHED THIS AND IT WAS SEVERAL WELL KNOWN PEOPLE TELLING YOU ABOUT GOING RAW, I HAVE READ SEVERAL BOOKS ON THE SUBJECT AND THIS DVD HAD NOTHING NEW IN IT. I WOULD SAVE MY MONEY $29 AND GO ON LINE OR YOU TUBE AND PULL UP DAVID WOLF, YOU TUBE HAS DOZENS OF RAW INFORMATION
Title: Raw For Life: The Ultimate Encyclopedia of the Raw Food Lifestyle

reviewText: It was good, not great.  Had some good info, but not nearly proportionate to the cost.  Has some really good points of view, and information, and interviews.
summary: good raw food info, but not WOW
Title: Raw For Life: The Ultimate Encyclopedia of the Raw Food Lifestyle
